text: Zanele Vimbela (born 28 April 1989) is a South African netball player. She has featured for the South Africa national netball team on several occasions, most notably in the 2014 Commonwealth Games and 2018 Commonwealth Games, as well as the 2019 Netball World Cup. ==References== Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:Commonwealth Games competitors for South Africa Category:Netball players at the 2014 Commonwealth Games Category:Netball players at the 2018 Commonwealth Games Category:Sportspeople from Johannesburg Category:South African netball players Category:Netball Superleague players Category:TeamBath netball players Category:Sirens Netball players Category:2019 Netball World Cup players Category:South African expatriate sportspeople in England Category:South African expatriate sportspeople in Scotland
